note 13. all other liabilities
this caption includes liabilities for various items including non-current compensation and benefits, deferred income, interest on tax liabilities, unrecognized tax benefits, environmental remediation, asset retirement obligations, derivative instruments, product warranties and a variety of sundry items.
accruals for non-current compensation and benefits amounted to $39,460 million and $39,430 million at december 31, 2012 and 2011, respectively. these amounts include postretirement benefits, pension accruals, and other compensation and benefit accruals such as deferred incentive compensation. see note 12.
we are involved in numerous remediation actions to clean up hazardous wastes as required by federal and state laws. liabilities for remediation costs exclude possible insurance recoveries and, when dates and amounts of such costs are not known, are not discounted. when there appears to be a range of possible costs with equal likelihood, liabilities are based on the low end of such range. it is reasonably possible that our environmental remediation exposure will exceed amounts accrued.however, due to uncertainties about the status of laws, regulations, technology and information related to individual sites, such amounts are not reasonably estimable. total reserves related to environmental remediation, including asbestos claims, were $2,988 millionat december 31, 2012.
